from the one that we have today. They didn't conceive of time as a progression, as a series

08:15.880 --> 08:23.300
of causes and effects. For instance, the future. To a classical Greek, the future was going

08:23.300 --> 08:29.000
to be just about like the present. The idea of evolution was not part of their worldview.

08:29.300 --> 08:36.840
The future would be the same as the present. The past was also different to them. Today,

08:37.120 --> 08:43.340
if a science fiction author or a creative writer wanted to reproduce something or write

08:43.340 --> 08:50.900
about the past, he may take his hero back into the past, a traveling process. That would

08:50.900 --> 08:54.140
not be alien to the Greeks. All they would have to do if they wanted to see somebody

08:54.140 --> 08:58.700
